<h2 class="sectionedit1"><a name="basic_stringnpos" id="basic_stringnpos">basic_string::npos</a></h2>
<div class="level2">
<pre class="cpp code cpp"><span class="kw4">static</span> <span class="kw4">const</span> size_type npos <span class="sy1">=</span> <span class="sy2">-</span><span class="nu0">1</span><span class="sy4">;</span></pre>
<p>
This is a special value that indicates maximum representable value by <code>size_type</code> type. When used as an argument to <code>basic_string</code> functions, it usually means “as many as possible” or “until the end of the string”. When used as a return value, it usually indicates failure.

</p>

